Installation
=================
To install the "Highlighter plugin" extension follow these simple steps:

 1. Upload the extension using the Administration panel
 2. Install the Highlighter extension


Introduction 
=============
Highlighter is an extension that helps developers to display code on their website.

The Plugin uses the <a target="_blank" href="http://alexgorbatchev.com/SyntaxHighlighter">Javascript SyntaxHighlighter by Alex Gorbatchev</a>
to highlight source code in your content.  

Please read its docu to get more information on how to style code blocks properly.

Usage
===============
Activate the Highlighter in your template:

$this->highlighter()->addBrush('Php')->activate();

IMPORTANT: You need to call this <u>before</u> your HTML &lt;head&gt; is rendered!

And then add content to your page that looks like this:

&lt;pre class="brush: php"&gt;
    &lt;?php
        $name = "Hello" . ' ' . "World"; 
        echo $name;
    ?&gt; 
&lt;/pre&gt;

